{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01RviGrbAnkMzbQakYU85Yjv","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tid: PRD-560.4\n3\ttitle: Update .gitignore patterns for .jsonl transcripts\n4\tkind: task\n5\tstatus: ready\n6\tpriority: medium\n7\teffort: xs\n8\tcapability: trivial\n9\tparent: \"[[PRD-560-transcripts-should-be-jsonl-files]]\"\n10\tdepends_on: []\n11\tblocks: []\n12\timpacts:\n13\t  - .gitignore\n14\tworkflow:\n15\ttarget_version:\n16\tcreated: 2026-04-09\n17\tupdated: 2026-04-09\n18\ttags: []\n19\t---\n20\t\n21\t# Update .gitignore patterns for .jsonl transcripts\n22\t\n23\t## Summary\n24\t\n25\tUpdate `.gitignore` to ignore `.jsonl` transcript files in the transient `.harness-transcripts/` directory, matching the new file extension introduced by PRD-560.1. Remove or update any existing `.log`-specific ignore patterns for transcripts.\n26\t\n27\t## Requirements\n28\t\n29\t1. Add or update `.gitignore` entries so that `.harness-transcripts/*.jsonl` files are ignored.\n30\t2. If there are existing ignore patterns for `.harness-transcripts/*.log`, update them to `.jsonl` or add the `.jsonl` pattern alongside (to cover both old and new files).\n31\t3. Ensure committed transcripts in `.darkfactory/transcripts/` are NOT ignored (they should be tracked by git).\n32\t\n33\t## Technical Approach\n34\t\n35\t### File: `.gitignore`\n36\t\n37\t1. Search for existing `.harness-transcripts` patterns in `.gitignore`.\n38\t2. If a pattern like `.harness-transcripts/*.log` or `.harness-transcripts/` exists, ensure `.jsonl` files are also covered. The simplest approach is to ignore the entire `.harness-transcripts/` directory if not already done.\n39\t3. Verify that `.darkfactory/transcripts/` is not ignored.\n40\t\n41\t## Acceptance Criteria\n42\t\n43\t- [ ] AC-1: `.harness-transcripts/*.jsonl` files are ignored by git.\n44\t- [ ] AC-2: Committed transcripts in `.darkfactory/transcripts/` remain tracked.\n45\t- [ ] AC-3: No transient transcript files (old `.log` or new `.jsonl`) appear in `git status` after a run.\n46\t\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1c5c88d4-1abd-4998-b1eb-b001b5a4f5e5","uuid":"57664625-75c6-45d1-b80b-6c5e3373e835","timestamp":"2026-04-09T07:56:24.333Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/sksizer2/Developer/DarkFactory/.darkfactory/prds/PRD-560.4-update-gitignore-patterns.md","content":"---\nid: PRD-560.4\ntitle: Update .gitignore patterns for .jsonl transcripts\nkind: task\nstatus: ready\npriority: medium\neffort: xs\ncapability: trivial\nparent: \"[[PRD-560-transcripts-should-be-jsonl-files]]\"\ndepends_on: []\nblocks: []\nimpacts:\n  - .gitignore\nworkflow:\ntarget_version:\ncreated: 2026-04-09\nupdated: 2026-04-09\ntags: []\n---\n\n# Update .gitignore patterns for .jsonl transcripts\n\n## Summary\n\nUpdate `.gitignore` to ignore `.jsonl` transcript files in the transient `.harness-transcripts/` directory, matching the new file extension introduced by PRD-560.1. Remove or update any existing `.log`-specific ignore patterns for transcripts.\n\n## Requirements\n\n1. Add or update `.gitignore` entries so that `.harness-transcripts/*.jsonl` files are ignored.\n2. If there are existing ignore patterns for `.harness-transcripts/*.log`, update them to `.jsonl` or add the `.jsonl` pattern alongside (to cover both old and new files).\n3. Ensure committed transcripts in `.darkfactory/transcripts/` are NOT ignored (they should be tracked by git).\n\n## Technical Approach\n\n### File: `.gitignore`\n\n1. Search for existing `.harness-transcripts` patterns in `.gitignore`.\n2. If a pattern like `.harness-transcripts/*.log` or `.harness-transcripts/` exists, ensure `.jsonl` files are also covered. The simplest approach is to ignore the entire `.harness-transcripts/` directory if not already done.\n3. Verify that `.darkfactory/transcripts/` is not ignored.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] AC-1: `.harness-transcripts/*.jsonl` files are ignored by git.\n- [ ] AC-2: Committed transcripts in `.darkfactory/transcripts/` remain tracked.\n- [ ] AC-3: No transient transcript files (old `.log` or new `.jsonl`) appear in `git status` after a run.\n","numLines":46,"startLine":1,"totalLines":46}}}
